-- Tepco president to be replaced by Managing Dir Nishizawa-Kyodo
-- 
-- Fri May 20, 2011 2:35am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/05/20/us-tepco-president-idUSTRE74J12H20110520

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Japan's Tokyo Electric Power, operator of the crippled Fukushima Daiichi nuclear power plant, is set to appoint Managing Director Toshio Nishizawa to replace President Masataka Shimizu, Kyodo News agency reported on Friday. 

 (Reporting by  Chang-Ran Kim ; Editing by Edmund Klamann)